Colombia ' s Simesa 1996 net profit rises . Siderugica de Medellin SA ( Simesa ) , Colombia ' s third largest steel manufacturer , said its net profit rose to 2 . 51 billion pesos in 1996 from 2 . 09 billion in 1995 . A company statement reporting the earnings said it had notified Colombia ' s Securities Superintendency that it plans to pay out 1 . 76 billion of the ' 96 profit in dividends and leave the rest , about 30 percent , in reserve for future investment projects . The dividend would amount to 24 pesos per share , it said . ( ( - - Javier Mozzo , Bogota newsroom , 571 610 7944 ) ) 
